RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 75. Claiming Purse 18384. FOR REGISTERED STATE BRED THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MILTON STREET settled off the pace in the opening quarter, given cue to pick up the tempo entering the turn, roused forward into closer contention, dug in three to four wide in upper stretch, gained command past the furlong marker and finished going away. TWIRLING CHIEF was well reserved racing in the back through early stages, continued well off the pace around the turn, cut the corner and given cue entering the lane, responded willingly, roused forward into close contention but could not move on with the winner. LURCH raced off the early pace, hustled up three to four wide around the turn, sustained a steady bid down the lane and cleared the rest. JUST JOHNNY raced up close running through the backstretch, flattened out around the turn, dropped back then passed a couple faders. PRAIRIE WOLF took over the lead midway up the backstretch, held clear around the turn, got collared by the winner past the furlong marker and had nothing left in reserve. CATALE led the way to the mid-way point up the backstretch then conceded position to PRAIRIE WOLF, remained forwardly placed around the turn then came up empty in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Twirling Chief
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved in back, inside bid into stretch, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Just Johnny
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close early, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Milton Street
ENTRY.COMMENT: pick up pace 3/8p, 3-4wd bid, going away

ENTRY.COMMENT: off pace, 3-4wd move turn, stayed on

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace, clear, tired final 1/8

ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed, faded lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PRAIRIE MEADOWS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 12000. FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BILLY YANK raced three wide entering the first turn, rated off the top trio up the backstretch, loomed up boldly near the quarter pole, hustled along three wide into the drive, took command approaching the eight pole, edged ahead and held late. SWEET DYNASTY was off a step slow and saved ground around the first turn, was unhurried and allowed to settle in the back of the pack, picked up the tempo entering the far turn, circled up four wide near the quarter pole, roused forward into slower contention, sustained a steady bid and was getting to the winner late. SKYLINE led the way around the first turn, set the pace up the backstretch and continued to hold off challengers around the far turn, got collared by the eventual winner approaching the eighth pole but ran on and finished well clear over the rest. BRILLIANT COLORS stalked the leader to the far turn, hustled along two wide into upper stretch then retreated. CALLE DE BOYD tracked the pace along the inside in early stages, cut the corner entering the lane, had no response and steadily faded.
